OL,6,F"I just felt the response I got wasn't
OL,7,Fvery receptive," Hatton says. "We did
OL,8,Fdisagree, but I didn't feel my
OL,9,Fconcerns or my thoughts were being
OL,10,Flistened to."
OL,12,FIt's a moment Hatton credits as one of
OL,13,Fthe first that sparked his interest in
OL,14,Fpolitics: "I suppose when you don't
OL,15,Ffeel you're being represented
OL,16,Feffectively you think maybe we should
OL,17,Fhave a different person and a
OL,18,Fdifferent outlook.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/9
