OL,6,FWithin weeks of winning the general
OL,7,Felection, the new Labour government
OL,8,Fannounced it would end use of the
OL,9,Fbarge in January 2025.
OL,11,F"We knew that if the barge had stayed
OL,12,Faround for much longer and the
OL,13,Fcontract had been extended, it would
OL,14,Fhave cost the taxpayer an extra
OL,15,F#20million just next year alone.
OL,17,F"That's a really big amount of money
OL,18,Fand it would have been a complete
OL,19,Fwaste, so it was really important that
OL,20,Fwe made that decision."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/9
